author: Inside Edition
description: Donald Glover, aka Childish Gambino, made a stunning announcement to an audience this weekend. The recording artist was performing at the Camp Flog Gnaw festival in Los Angeles when he took a moment to talk to the crowd, telling them he suffered a stroke last year, causing him to cancel his tour. He said, "I couldn’t really see well, so when we went to Houston, I went to the hospital and the doctor was like, ‘You had a stroke.’” Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Donald Glover, AKA Childish Gambino, Says He Had A Stroke

author: Inside Edition
description: Melinda Howard says she was breaking down cardboard boxes for recycling at her new house in Mississippi when she nicked her hand. The 63-year-old ultra marathoner wrapped her hand with a bandage. A week later, her hand started hurting, and she went to urgent care. What made Howard's infection so severe is the fact that for years, she had been taking the steroid prednisone, which is commonly prescribed to reduce inflammation, but one side effect is that it thins the skin.
title: Woman Rushed To Urgent Care After Getting Paper Cut

author: Inside Edition
description: There are lots of examples on the internet of people getting big surprises when their Christmas trees burst open. Sometimes, the sheer force of the unwrapping knocks over the people and things in its path. Inside Edition got some tips on how to make the unwrapping of a tree at home less of an explosive event. The holiday season officially kicked-off at the White House Monday when First Lady Melania Trump welcomed the White House Christmas tree.
title: Tips To Safely Unwrap Your Christmas Tree

author: Inside Edition
description: Tatiana Schlossberg, the 35-year-old granddaughter of John F. Kennedy and daughter of Caroline Kennedy, revealed she has terminal cancer. The mom of two wrote in a New Yorker essay, published on the 62nd anniversary of JFK's assassination, that she found out she has acute myeloid leukemia from a routine blood test after giving birth to her second child in May of 2024. The Kennedys have a long history of tragedy, and Schlossberg says she dreads bringing more sadness to her mother.
title: Tatiana Schlossberg, JFK's Grandchild, Reveals She Has Terminal Cancer

author: Inside Edition
description: The grandparents of the teenager found dead during a Caribbean cruise spoke out in an interview with ABC News. They confirmed Anna Kepner's 16-year-old stepbrother was sharing a stateroom where she died. They say the FBI told the family Kepner was choked to death, possibly with a bar hold maneuver. Kepner spent her last evening with her grandparents in the casino aboard the Carnival Horizon cruise ship. The next morning, they heard a chilling announcement.
title: Anna Kepner's Grandparents Talk About Her Death And Her Stepbrother

author: Inside Edition
description: Twenty-six-year-old business analyst Bethany Magee was set on fire during a horrific attack on a commuter train in Chicago. Police say a man poured gasoline over Magee on a Chicago L train.  Magee tried to fight off her attacker and fled but cops say the man followed her and set her ablaze. She was rushed to the hospital with burns covering 60% of her body. There's growing outrage Monday after it was revealed that the suspect is 50-year-old Lawrence Reed, a career criminal with 72 prior arrests.
title: Woman Set On Fire In Chicago Train Attack Identified

author: Inside Edition
description: Despite inflation, prices for turkeys are slightly down this year, but everything else is pretty much up. If you are trying to save a few bucks this Thanksgiving, some stores are offering dinner for 10 for the price of $40. That comes to $4 a person for a Thanksgiving feast. Inside Edition's Les Trent went to Walmart to see what you get. Inside Edition asked chef Lauren Covas to prepare the meal. Inside Edition also spoke to self-taught home cook August DeWindt.
title: Thanksgiving Meal Ideas That Won’t Break The Bank

author: Inside Edition
description: Authorities say Morgan Geyser, 23, cut off her ankle monitor and walked out of a group home on Saturday night. She was recaptured Sunday night at a truck stop in Illinois. Eleven years ago, Geyser and her adolescent friend stabbed classmate Payton Leutner 19 times, they said, to please the fictional horror character known as "Slenderman." Geyser was sent to a psychiatric hospital earlier this year before being placed in a group home. Geyser's lawyer, Tony Cotton, spoke with Inside Edition.
title: Lawyer of Assailant In 'Slenderman' Stabbing Case Speaks

author: Inside Edition
description: Firebrand Congresswoman Marjorie Taylor Greene abruptly called it quits after five years on Capitol Hill. So what's next for Greene? The speculation is rampant. Time Magazine quoted allies who say "she has considered running for president in 2028," but Greene shot down that prospect. In recent weeks she's made highly charged appearances on The View and CNN. Some believe that TV  is where her future lies.
title: What's Next For Congresswoman Marjorie Taylor Greene?

author: Inside Edition
description: Basketball stars had to compete for the audience's attention after this cutie popped up on the jumbotron during a Suns-Pacers game in Phoenix. Sterling, 3, was attending his first NBA game when he unexpectedly became the most popular fan of the night. His dad, Christopher, says he had no idea how much Sterling's little smiles and waves would ripple throughout social media. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: 3-Year-Old 'Popcorn Kid' Goes Viral After Jumbotron Appearance At NBA Game

author: Inside Edition
description: Jeremiah Coleman from Nashville, Tennessee, is defying odds after an injury at 9 years old left him blind.
title: Nashville Teen Who Lost Vision Joins School's Band #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: Anna Kepner's ex-boyfriend, Joshua Tew, spoke with Inside Edition following her funeral at a church outside Orlando, Florida.
title: Anna Kepner's Ex-Boyfriend Says Her Stepbrother Harassed Her #shorts
